    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Perry</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 36.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 17, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch of the 24th of September, No. 127, which informs me of your first
                    interview with Mr. Llorente, the new minister of state, for the reception of the
                    representatives of foreign powers. The assurances of good will towards our
                    country which were tendered to you in that interview are received with much
                    satisfaction.</p>
                <p>The sentiments whice Mr. Llorente expressed on that occasion in relation to the
                    difficulty between Spain and Peru were so just and wise that I cannot allow
                    myself to believe that the new administration will permit itself to remain under
                    embarrassment with a question for the satisfactory solution of which nothing
                    seems to be necessary to decide but which of the two parties shall first make a
                    formal overture towards mutual reconciliation.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horatio J. Perry</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
